Male genitalia (
Fig. 26
): Relatively short, moderately sclerotized. Median lobe broad, moderately arcuate, moderately distorted. Endophallus strongly folded, teeth not visible. Parameres of about same length, both slender, slightly twisted, asetose.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 37
): Coxostylus slightly sigmoid, dorso-ventrally moderately depressed, gently curved to apex, with one seta at apex, with one short but robust ensiform seta, with six nematiform setae medially.
